summary: An ordinance appropriating the sum of One Hundred Twenty-five ($125.00) Dollars of the general fund of the City of Seattle to pay the claim of Anna Donahoe for personal injuries received by her on the 1st day of July 1916, while walking on the sidewalks between Westlake Avenue and Terry Avenue North and near the alley that lies between said avenues about a dozen feet west of said alley, in the City of Seattle, and authorizing the drawing of a warrant therefor.
